The paper discusses a deep learning framework for causal discovery from incomplete data, which involves encoding cause-effect relations between events and predicting effects from a given action. This falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with missing data imputation, which is a common problem in data mining (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the simulations conducted in the paper involve both synthetic and real data, indicating a possible connection to social and information networks (cs.SI).
